        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 28 at 4:31PM MDT until July 28 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hobson, or 17
miles southeast of Stanford, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Hobson, Ackley Lake State Park, Moccasin, and Benchland.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
